 {"id":"asupersync-cpqu","title":"[EPIC] Chaos Testing Mode for Lab Runtime","description":"# Overview

An extension to LabReactor that can inject random delays, spurious wakeups,
simulated I/O errors, and cancellations at configurable rates - to stress-test
application code's resilience.

## Why This Matters

Production systems face chaos constantly:
- Network partitions
- Slow responses  
- OOM kills
- Race conditions
- Random failures

A chaos mode lets developers find these bugs BEFORE production. Combined with
deterministic replay, failures become REPRODUCIBLE.

## How It Works

```rust
Lab::new()
    .with_chaos(ChaosConfig {
        cancel_probability: 0.01,      // 1% random cancellation
        delay_probability: 0.05,       // 5% random delay
        delay_range: 1ms..100ms,
        io_error_probability: 0.02,    // 2% I/O error
        wakeup_storm_probability: 0.001, // 0.1% spurious wakeups
        seed: 12345,                   // REPRODUCIBLE chaos!
    })
    .run(|cx| async {
        // Application code with injected chaos
    });

// On failure:
// "Test failed with seed 12345. Replay with same seed to reproduce."
```

## Chaos Types

1. **Random Cancellation**: Inject CancelRequested at random times
2. **Random Delays**: Add latency at poll points
3. **I/O Errors**: Fail I/O operations randomly
4. **Wakeup Storms**: Spurious wakeups to test idempotency
5. **Budget Exhaustion**: Randomly exhaust budgets
6. **Clock Skew**: Virtual time jumps (for distributed scenarios)

## Determinism is Key

The chaos MUST be deterministic:
- Same seed = same chaos sequence
- Same test = same failures
- Enables debugging of intermittent issues

This is the killer combination: chaos + deterministic replay.

## Integration with Existing Features

- Uses LabReactor's virtual time
- Uses LabReactor's deterministic scheduling
- Integrates with cancellation injection (#1)
- Reports via tracing (#2)
- Verified by oracles

## Success Criteria

- [ ] Configurable chaos parameters
- [ ] Deterministic with same seed
- [ ] All chaos types implemented
- [ ] Integrates with Lab infrastructure
- [ ] Clear failure reporting with seed
- [ ] Documentation with examples","notes":"Chaos testing mode complete: (1) ChaosConfig with all builder methods for configurable parameters; (2) Deterministic chaos with seed-based reproducibility; (3) All core chaos types implemented - cancellation, delays, I/O errors, wakeup storms, budget exhaustion; (4) Full Lab infrastructure integration via LabConfig.with_chaos(); (5) ChaosStats for clear failure reporting; (6) Comprehensive documentation and examples (asupersync-mzsl). Clock skew deferred to Phase 4 distributed work.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-18T17:58:11.895031374Z","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-20T18:38:27.511527754Z","closed_at":"2026-01-20T18:38:27.511436772Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-cpqu","depends_on_id":"asupersync-mzsl","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-27T06:20:43Z","created_by":"import"}]}
 {"id":"asupersync-cqq","title":"[Net] Implement TcpListener and TcpStream","description":"# TCP Implementation

## Overview
Full TCP networking with cancel-correct I/O obligations.

## TcpListener

```rust
pub struct TcpListener {
    inner: sys::TcpListener,
}

impl TcpListener {
    /// Bind to address
    pub async fn bind(addr: impl ToSocketAddrs) -> io::Result<Self>;

    /// Accept connection (returns obligation)
    pub async fn accept(&self) -> io::Result<(TcpStream, SocketAddr)>;

    /// Get local address
    pub fn local_addr(&self) -> io::Result<SocketAddr>;

    /// Set TTL
    pub fn set_ttl(&self, ttl: u32) -> io::Result<()>;

    /// Incoming connections as stream
    pub fn incoming(&self) -> Incoming<'_>;
}

/// Stream of incoming connections
pub struct Incoming<'a> {
    listener: &'a TcpListener,
}

impl Stream for Incoming<'_> {
    type Item = io::Result<TcpStream>;
}
```

## TcpStream

```rust
pub struct TcpStream {
    inner: sys::TcpStream,
}

impl TcpStream {
    /// Connect to address
    pub async fn connect(addr: impl ToSocketAddrs) -> io::Result<Self>;

    /// Connect with timeout
    pub async fn connect_timeout(addr: SocketAddr, timeout: Duration) -> io::Result<Self>;

    /// Get peer address
    pub fn peer_addr(&self) -> io::Result<SocketAddr>;

    /// Get local address
    pub fn local_addr(&self) -> io::Result<SocketAddr>;

    /// Shutdown read/write/both
    pub fn shutdown(&self, how: Shutdown) -> io::Result<()>;

    /// Set TCP_NODELAY
    pub fn set_nodelay(&self, nodelay: bool) -> io::Result<()>;

    /// Set keepalive
    pub fn set_keepalive(&self, keepalive: Option<Duration>) -> io::Result<()>;

    /// Split into read/write halves
    pub fn split(&mut self) -> (ReadHalf<'_>, WriteHalf<'_>);

    /// Split with owned halves
    pub fn into_split(self) -> (OwnedReadHalf, OwnedWriteHalf);
}

impl AsyncRead for TcpStream { ... }
impl AsyncWrite for TcpStream { ... }
```

## TcpSocket (low-level)

```rust
pub struct TcpSocket {
    inner: sys::TcpSocket,
}

impl TcpSocket {
    /// Create new IPv4 socket
    pub fn new_v4() -> io::Result<Self>;

    /// Create new IPv6 socket
    pub fn new_v6() -> io::Result<Self>;

    /// Set SO_REUSEADDR
    pub fn set_reuseaddr(&self, reuseaddr: bool) -> io::Result<()>;

    /// Set SO_REUSEPORT
    #[cfg(unix)]
    pub fn set_reuseport(&self, reuseport: bool) -> io::Result<()>;

    /// Bind to address
    pub fn bind(&self, addr: SocketAddr) -> io::Result<()>;

    /// Listen (convert to TcpListener)
    pub fn listen(self, backlog: u32) -> io::Result<TcpListener>;

    /// Connect (convert to TcpStream)
    pub async fn connect(self, addr: SocketAddr) -> io::Result<TcpStream>;
}
```

## I/O Obligations

```rust
/// Accept obligation - pending connection acceptance
pub struct AcceptObligation {
    listener: Arc<TcpListener>,
    state: AcceptState,
}

impl AcceptObligation {
    /// Complete: accept the connection
    pub async fn complete(self) -> io::Result<(TcpStream, SocketAddr)>;

    /// Abort: reject the pending connection
    pub fn abort(self);
}

/// Read obligation - pending read operation
pub struct ReadObligation<'a> {
    stream: &'a TcpStream,
    buf: ReadBuf<'a>,
}

/// Write obligation - pending write with two-phase commit
pub struct WriteObligation<'a> {
    stream: &'a TcpStream,
    data: Vec<u8>,
}

impl WriteObligation<'_> {
    pub fn stage(&mut self, data: &[u8]);
    pub async fn commit(self) -> io::Result<usize>;
}
```

## Platform Abstraction

```rust
// src/net/sys/mod.rs
#[cfg(target_os = "linux")]
mod linux;
#[cfg(target_os = "macos")]
mod macos;
#[cfg(target_os = "windows")]
mod windows;

pub use platform::*;
```

## Cancel-Safety
- accept: cancel = no connection accepted (client retries)
- connect: cancel = connection attempt aborted
- read: cancel = partial data discarded (OK)
- write: use WriteObligation for atomic writes

